#: ../../Y/Your-mileage-may-vary.rst:5
msgid "Your mileage may vary"
msgstr "Your mileage may vary"

#: ../../Y/Your-mileage-may-vary.rst:7
msgid "cav\\."
msgstr "ことわざ"

#: ../../Y/Your-mileage-may-vary.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from the standard disclaimer attached to EPA mileage ratings by American "
"car manufacturers]"
msgstr "[アメリカの自動車メーカーがEPAの燃費評価に付ける標準的な免責事項から]"

#: ../../Y/Your-mileage-may-vary.rst:12
msgid ""
"A ritual warning often found in Unix freeware distributions. Translates "
"roughly as \"Hey, I tried to write this portably, but who knows what'll "
"happen on your system?\""
msgstr ""
"Unixのフリーウェア配布物によく見られる儀式的な警告。だいたい「いや、移植性を考えて書いたつもりだけど、きみのシステムで何が起こるかなんて誰にもわからないよ?」という意味になる。"

#: ../../Y/Your-mileage-may-vary.rst:16
msgid ""
"More generally, a qualifier attached to advice. \"I find that sending "
"flowers works well, but your mileage may vary.\""
msgstr ""
"より一般的には、助言に付け加えられる留保。「花を贈るのがうまくいくと私は思うが、きみの場合は違うかもしれない(your mileage may "
"vary)」。"
